market has leveled off and while women are earning an increasingly large share of bachelor's degrees overall the percentage of women earning degrees in some fields such as computer science has actually declined since the mid 1990s even women's state level political office holding seems to have peaked accompanying these trends there is evidence that americans attitudes towards acceptable roles for women have taken a conservative turn after decades of moving towards more egalitarian views donate make a donation social links facebook twitter youtube scribd contact serra house 589 capistrano way stanford ca 94305 8640 map 650 723 1994 gender email stanford edu
